rest_of_day_open: Probably uneventful. We aren't the type who go to bars or friends often, and of course that's limited for all places now anyhow. My husband is very high risk so he has been at home 24/7 except church on Sunday (in our car at the drive in). So we probably won't do much.
critical_positive: We both are easy going. She lives in Texas, I live in Oklahoma. We’re not too different in age-four years I think. She happens to play Xbox also as well as I do. We even play some of the same games. She has a dog and likes animals, though her dog is much smaller than mine are-about the same size as my dog’s poop LOL. It was fun.
critical_negative: Everything went pretty well so I don’t know what I’m supposed to say or how I’m supposed to use up 50 words before I can continue.  But everything went well as for our conversation and personalities.  It was actually good and everything matched up well and was easy to hold for over the 25 minutes

rest_of_day_open: The rest of my week should be pretty good. I'm hopeful because I have some testing this week for a possible job. So I'm excited about that. I think the rest of the week will be productive. I guess overall I feel the week will be positive and I'll be productive. I guess this week will be a little exciting too.
critical_positive: I think us being similar in age helped with our conversation, also I think conversation came more easily because we both seemed pretty outgoing and interested in the whole experience. We also had some similar interests and both being night owls helped. We live in close to the same part of the country too.
critical_negative: Well I think our nervousness, in the beginning, made it a tiny bit hard but that lasted a very short time. In the beginning she was all over the place talking to her husband at the same time in the background. I think that was mostly due to nerves on her end.
